    "title": "Hiring Production Engineer at Dabur India Consulting Pvt Ltd",
    "description": "Dabur India Consulting Pvt Ltd is actively seeking a talented and motivated Production Engineer to join our dynamic team in Delhi. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Dabur India Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nDabur India Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Oversee daily production operations to meet output targets\n• Ensure product quality meets internal and customer specifications\n• Coordinate with design and engineering teams on product improvements\n• Prepare production cost analysis and efficiency reports\n• Manage supplier quality audits and vendor development\n• Conduct root cause analysis for quality rejections and defects\n• Ensure compliance with safety regulations and factory acts\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• BPharm / MPharm / PharmD\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in APQP\n• Proficiency in PLC/SCADA\n• Proficiency in SolidWorks\n• Proficiency in GD&T\n• Proficiency in Six Sigma\n• Proficiency in Statistical Process Control\n• Proficiency in Kaizen\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Referral bonus program\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Delhi, Delhi, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Dabur India Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
